
Chapter 5: CSS Text Properties

1. text-align property:

the text-align property defines the direction of text in the webpage.

6 Values of text-align property::

1. center - change direction of text to center in x-axis from left to right.
2. left - set bydefault - direction is left 
3. right - change direction of text to right
4. start - change direction of text to left
5. end - change direction of text to right
6. justify - balanced left and right margins

More About Text Align Property:

the text align property depends on parent element.
the alignment does not change according to the doucment but change according to the parent element like body tag. 
our text's parent element is the body tag
and our texts are the child tags of body tag


